 is shaped by individual characteristics that shape one's risk aversion.
 In a rather canonical formulation, we set up only one random process 
\begin_inset Formula $W$
\end_inset

 which affects all individuals in the economy.
 Such a process could represent the macroeconomic changes in the economy
 such as proliferation of new occupations, onslaught of calamities, rise
