 such as economic depression or even political uncertainties.
 The gains and losses in this economy are treated as a repeated lottery
 to be played by the consumers as the same events are observed by them simultane
ously.
 The random process is a simple Bernoulli trial with probability 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 (i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $E(W)=p$
\end_inset

) and the uncertainty among the consumers influences their decision to position
 themselves to benefit from gains in the economy or to seek protection from
 the losses the economy is exposed to.
 Given a disposable income 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

